answers.body_markdown:
Presumably you have an earlier call to **startTransaction**, don&#39;t you?

The problem is that the addition of the Part is recorded by the **UndoManager** and therefore is undone or redone.  I think you want to temporarily set **Diagram.skipsUndoManager** to true, add the background picture, and then set it back.

Another way of doing this:
```
myDiagram.commit(d =&gt; {
  d.add(...);
}, null);
```
https://gojs.net/latest/api/symbols/Diagram.html#commit

And yet a third possibility: add the Part to the &quot;Grid&quot; layer, for which **Layer.isTemporary** is true, so any changes in the layer are not recorded by the **UndoManager**. https://gojs.net/latest/api/symbols/Layer.html#isTemporary

So just change the **layerName** to &quot;Grid&quot;. I think you also need to set its **Part.position**. And then no transaction is needed.

