Finally I solved it; I post the solution hoping it may be useful.

It is possible to enable overlays on existing ListView items:
send a `LVM_SETITEMSTATE` message with: index of the existing item, `LVIS_OVERLAYMASK` as mask, and overlay index as value.
The overlay index for a file may be read calling the `IShellIconOverlay::GetOverlayIndex` functon; 
or it is also possible to retrieve it from the same call to `SHGetFileInfo`, using the `SHGFI_OVERLAYINDEX` and `SHGFI_ICON` flags;
it is also possible to retreve the index of a specific overlay only once, because it will be constant on the system; 
for example the &quot;link&quot; overlay has always index = 2 on my system.
The overlay index value must be passed using the `INDEXTOOVERLAYMASK` modifier (i.e. left shifted by 8).
